<p>Using PHP + Doctrine I get this:</p>  <pre><code>    //retrieve data     $entityManager = $this-&gt;getEntityManager();     $all = $entityManager-&gt;getRepository('\Entity\ServiceType')-&gt;findAll();     foreach($all as $value)         $options[$value-&gt;getId()] = $value-&gt;getServiceType(); </code></pre>  <p>Autocomplete within IDE does not suggest methods that follow <code>-&gt;</code>, namely things like <code>getId()</code>, and <code>getServiceType()</code>.</p>  <p>And PHP does not offer (easy) casting to desired type....</p>